metadata.name: Living City #6
metadata.description:
It is a "Living City"

The state of the city sky will change by receiving your current time.
For example, if it is morning in your city, the sun will rise in your mint, and if it is night, your mint will be dark.

The settings are such that at 06:00 in your geographical area, the sun rises and the sky slowly brightens, and at 19:00 in your geographical area, the sky darkens and the sun sets. In the rest of the night, the moon will shine in the sky and the position of the moon in the sky will change every hour of the night.

To see this effect better, you can take a photo of each watch and compare the photos.

- Press “s” to save the current canvas.

* Note: If it is night in your geographical location, you will definitely see the minted pieces with a dark sky with the moon, and if it is day, you will see a bright sky with a random background color with the sun.

--
Artist: Pointiago
Aug 02, 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: blinksquare 2022 #88
metadata.description:
From the pixel-lab vault - evolved from 'blinksquare' (2008) 
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image (for printing)

Right-click: Save/Copy the image

A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine,
written in vanilla JavaScript some more info in the source-code
- The work will refresh and restart after some time -
-------------------------------------------------

I created 'blinksquare' back in 2008 in Secondlife,
it was like a kinetic 3D sculpture; that would change over time.

I wanted to do a 2022 remake; and while working on it; it evolved a bit.
Also inspired by writing and ancient Hieroglyphs from around the world 


xxx Amsterdam chillout


For the love of Art, hugging someone you love, and filling that RGB-and Z buffer  ^__^

metadata.name: Ripple #70
metadata.description:
A small study into Pointillism (patterns) and moiré effects with simple circles, closed and dashed lines, creating landscapes like decorative fireworks in the skies and ripples in smooth water.

Ripple is exclusively for collectors of *the seed* A quarterly zine by @aethersovereign & @arielmalka dedicated to generative art on the #fxhash platform, also an interactive #genart experiment in its own right.

Press s in live mode for a 2000x2000 download

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2
&density=3

Lammetje August 2022

metadata.name: Ornamental Tree #47
metadata.description:
A simple tree in a grassy field. Released as a thank you gift to holders of Orchard, Grove, and Deep Forest.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px

Common Features:
- One of three seasons: spring, summer, or fall
- 50/50 square or circle shaped trees
- Percent distance haze
- Neutral or blue sky color
- 50/50 color or background tinted clouds
- Color tints for highlights and shadows
- If spring or summer, 50/50 chance of flowers
- Smooth rolling hills or not

metadata.name: Ongemak #77
metadata.description:
Wabi-sabi (侘寂): appreciate impermanence and imperfection

There is little chance of a 'perfect' work of art. The small imperfections require reflection. 

The variation and randomness give the work some asymmetry, common in wabi-sabi esthetics. Because of a limited color palette and the simple shapes used, the works keep their simplicity (another principle of wabi-sabi). The noisy texture gives it some roughness, indeed again a core principle of wabi-sabi. 

The colors are reminiscent of the 70s and 80s. Some think that everything was better in the past. The trick is to enjoy the moment.

Thinking about impermanence is sometimes uncomfortable, 'ongemak' in Dutch, but also valuable.

metadata.name: SoulSea #178
metadata.description:
The Soul Sea

You look down and find that the ocean in your heart is a sine wave. 
The tide gently laps onto the shore.

The soul is the sea. You are the land. 
There are waves on the shore, and the waves are slices.

Gazing at the slices, you feel the coldness of the Arctic Ocean, the permafrost of the Antarctic Sea, the deep darkness of the bottomless sea.

Stay silent, hear the sound of the waves lapping at the innumerable shores far away.
Feel the soul of the digital ocean.

Interactivities:
> Key P: Pause
> Key S: Save
> Press and move mouseX: wave moves slower / faster

Che-Yu Wu
